# 🧠 The Simple Mental Model of AWS

> 💡 **Memorize this flow. Most internet systems follow it.**

```
Internet
   ↓
DNS
   ↓
Load Balancer
   ↓
Application Servers
   ↓
Database / Storage
```

Everything in AWS exists to support **this architecture**.

---

# 🌍 PART 1 — AWS GLOBAL INFRASTRUCTURE

## Architecture

```
AWS Global Network
        │
        ▼
Regions
        │
        ▼
Availability Zones
        │
        ▼
Data Centers
        │
        ▼
Physical Servers
```

---

<details>
<summary>❓ Why AWS Designed It This Way</summary>

Traditional hosting problems:

❌ One datacenter failure = full outage
❌ Limited scalability
❌ Disaster risk

AWS solution:

✔ Multiple regions
✔ Multiple AZs
✔ Infrastructure isolation

</details>

---

### 🧠 Memory Trick

```
Region > AZ > Datacenter > Server
```

---

# 🏢 PART 2 — PHYSICAL DATACENTER ARCHITECTURE

Inside an AWS datacenter:

```
Rack
 ├── Physical Server
 │
 ├── CPU
 ├── RAM
 ├── NVMe SSD
 └── Network Card
```

Thousands of racks exist in one facility.

---

<details>
<summary>❓ Why massive datacenters exist</summary>

Companies like:

* streaming platforms
* social networks
* global SaaS systems

need **millions of compute instances**.

AWS infrastructure supports this scale.

</details>

---

# ⚙️ PART 3 — HYPERVISOR (NITRO SYSTEM)

```
Physical Server
     │
     ▼
Hypervisor
     │
     ▼
Multiple Virtual Machines
```

AWS uses **Nitro Hypervisor**.

---

### 🧠 Memory Trick

```
Server = Building
VMs = Apartments
Hypervisor = Building manager
```

---

# 🌐 PART 4 — VIRTUAL PRIVATE CLOUD (VPC)

Your **private network in AWS**.

```
AWS Region
    │
    ▼
VPC (10.0.0.0/16)
    │
    ├── Public Subnet
    └── Private Subnet
```

---

<details>
<summary>❓ Why VPC exists</summary>

Companies require:

* network isolation
* IP management
* routing control
* firewall rules

A VPC behaves like a **private corporate network**.

</details>

---

# 🔀 PART 5 — SUBNETS

Subnets divide the VPC.

```
VPC
 │
 ├── Public Subnet
 │      ├── Load Balancer
 │      └── Web Servers
 │
 └── Private Subnet
        ├── App Servers
        └── Database
```

---

### Security Architecture

```
Internet
   ↓
Public Subnet
   ↓
Private Subnet
   ↓
Database
```

---

# 🌍 PART 6 — INTERNET GATEWAY

Gateway connecting VPC to internet.

```
Internet
   │
   ▼
Internet Gateway
   │
   ▼
Route Table
   │
   ▼
Public Subnet
```

Think of it as the **VPC's front door**.

---

# 🔁 PART 7 — NAT GATEWAY

Allows private servers to access internet **securely**.

```
Private EC2
     │
     ▼
NAT Gateway
     │
     ▼
Internet
```

✔ outbound traffic allowed
❌ inbound traffic blocked

---

# 🔐 PART 8 — SECURITY LAYERS

Two levels of security.

| Layer          | Scope    |
| -------------- | -------- |
| Security Group | Instance |
| Network ACL    | Subnet   |

---

### Security Group

```
EC2
 │
 ▼
Security Group
```

✔ Stateful firewall

---

### Network ACL

```
Subnet
 │
 ▼
Network ACL
```

✔ Stateless firewall

